{
  "V1": {
    "authors": [
      "Jody Robbins"
    ],
    "body": {
      "summary": [
        "Canadian Rockies resort completes a sweeping property-wide overhaul after devastating 2024 wildfire"
      ],
      "sections": [
        {
          "headline": [],
          "paragraphs": [
            "One of North America’s iconic Rocky Mountain resorts has emerged from its most ambitious overhaul in decades. Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge officially reopened this week following a $100-million, property-wide transformation.",
            "Set on 700 acres inside Jasper National Park, Canada’s second-most-visited national park with 2.4 million visitors annually has long catered to travellers who want nature on their doorstep and a spa steps away.",
            "The revamp comes after the property suffered damage during the 2024 wildfire that tore through the national park, destroying roughly 30 per cent of Jasper. Several buildings, including staff housing, were affected."
          ]
        },
        {
          "headline": [
            "A design overhaul rooted in place"
          ],
          "paragraphs": [
            "More than 330 of the resort’s 397 guest rooms, suites and signature cabins have been redesigned from the ground up, with what the property calls alpine-chic interiors that prioritize privacy. The design reflects the local landscape beyond the expansive windows, with blue tones inspired by nearby glacial lakes, carved-wood details and organic textures.",
            "The iconic Signature Cabins, including Outlook Cabin and Point Cabin, remain storied spots that continue to attract multi-generational groups, special-occasion stays and high-profile guests, such as Queen Elizabeth 2, who stayed in the Outlook Cabin in 2005.",
            "The reimagined Main Lodge lobby and a new lakeside patio overlooking Lac Beauvert and Whistlers Mountain offer guests postcard-worthy panoramic views upon arrival."
          ]
        },
        {
          "headline": [
            "Dining options at Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge"
          ],
          "paragraphs": [
            "The dining scene has undergone a full overhaul, with three new signature restaurants replacing the former food and beverage lineup. Elderwood takes over the Great Hall, a timber-framed room built for leisurely, family-friendly meals of regionally inspired dishes under soaring beams.",
            "Lume, named for Jasper’s ever-changing light, occupies the former Emerald Lounge and offers a plant-forward menu and cocktails.",
            "The Barbicon leans into the classic mountain steak house format, anchored by the original 1922 Tyndall stone fireplace and a menu built around slow-crafted techniques and aged ingredients. It’s named after Barbican Pass, an alpine pass high in the Canadian Rockies for the geographically curious."
          ]
        },
        {
          "headline": [
            "Wellness in the wilderness"
          ],
          "paragraphs": [
            "The resort’s Wellness Without Walls philosophy, which treats nature as the primary vehicle for restoration, is front and centre in the new programming.",
            "Wellness offerings include a guided Glacial Plunge and Sauna Journey on the shores of Lac Beauvert, along with expanded guided stargazing, fitting for a resort within one of the world’s designated Dark Sky Preserves. Indigenous foraging experiences, accessed by helicopter, push the wellness programming into new territory.",
            "Beyond that, the quintessential Canadian Rockies activities—hiking, canoeing, kayaking and skiing—are all on offer. The new Embark Outpost + Provisions serves as base camp, with an adventure concierge, locally roasted coffee and trail supplies. Camp JPL Adventure Club for kids ages 5 to 12 opens later this summer. The Stanley Thompson-designed golf course has been meticulously restored, and new pickleball courts and a playground have also been added.",
            "“There is something deeply restorative about arriving in Jasper,” says the resort’s general manager Garrett Turta. “At Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge, luxury has always been less about excess and more about what people rediscover while they’re here: time together, space to breathe, connection to nature and a slower rhythm of life. This new chapter builds on that feeling, creating a resort experience that feels both deeply connected to memory and entirely new to discover.”"
          ]
        },
        {
          "headline": [
            "A major investment"
          ],
          "paragraphs": [
            "The $100-million project is the latest in a series of investments by the lodge’s owner, Oxford Properties, which has committed to spending more than $2B since 2025.",
            "“When you invest in a place like Jasper, with such deep ties to Canada and its history, you take on a responsibility that goes well beyond the property itself. We’re proud of this extensive transformation, which reflects not only our long-term conviction in timeless, elevated hospitality experiences, but also our commitment to Canadian communities like Jasper,” said Tyler MacDonald, senior vice president and head of hotels at Oxford Properties.",
            "Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge is now open."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
